/dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the list\", \"from\": 4352, \"to\": 4360}, {\"ngram\": \"complaints\", \"from\": 4364, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"the poster\", \"from\": 4381, \"to\": 4391}, {\"ngram\": \"a stylised panorama\", \"from\": 4406, \"to\": 4425}, {\"ngram\": \"the absence\", \"from\": 4439, \"to\": 4450}, {\"ngram\": \"the cross\", \"from\": 4454, \"to\": 4463}, {\"ngram\": \"the Dome des Invalides\", \"from\": 4479, \"to\": 4501}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What is the point of holding the Olympic Games in France if we then hide who we are?\\\"\", \"from\": 4530, \"to\": 4616, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4581, \"end\": 4587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.941716133673768, \"rank\": 0.061734972251580505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the point\", \"from\": 4539, \"to\": 4548}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 4560, \"to\": 4577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marion Marechal of the far-right Reconquete (Reconquest) party posted on X.\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4692, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Marion Marechal\", \"from\": 4617, \"to\": 4632}, {\"ngram\": \"the far-right Reconquete (Reconquest) party\", \"from\": 4636, \"to\": 4679}, {\"ngram\": \"X.\", \"from\": 4690, \"to\": 4692}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, National Rally (RN) lawmaker Nicolas Meizonnet wrote that the omissions must be the result of \\\"wokism\\\".\", \"from\": 4694, \"to\": 4808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4705, \"end\": 4719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Rally\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Rally\"}, {\"begin\": 4734, \"end\": 4751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Meizonnet\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Meizonnet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the omissions\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 4776}, {\"ngram\": \"the result\", \"from\": 4785, \"to\": 4795}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"wokism\", \"from\": 4799, \"to\": 4806}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This again... For those of you hearing that reappropriated term bandied about all the time as the root cause of everything wrong with the modern world we live in, know that it did not use to be a bad thing.\", \"from\": 4810, \"to\": 5017, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that reappropriated term\", \"from\": 4849, \"to\": 4873}, {\"ngram\": \"all the time\", \"from\": 4888, \"to\": 4900}, {\"ngram\": \"the root cause\", \"from\": 4904, \"to\": 4918}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 4922, \"to\": 4932}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern world\", \"from\": 4944, \"to\": 4960}, {\"ngram\": \"a bad thing\", \"from\": 5004, \"to\": 5015}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It still is not.\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5034, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The term is derived from African-American Vernacular English, used in racial justice movements in the early to mid-1900s.\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5157, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5061, \"end\": 5096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"African-American Vernacular English\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/African-American_Vernacular_English\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The term\", \"from\": 5036, \"to\": 5044}, {\"ngram\": \"racial justice movements\", \"from\": 5106, \"to\": 5130}, {\"ngram\": \"mid-1900s\", \"from\": 5147, \"to\": 5156}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be \\\"woke\\\" politically in the Black community means that someone is informed, educated and conscious of social injustice and racial inequality, as Merriam-Webster Dictionary defines.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5342, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Black community\", \"from\": 5186, \"to\": 5205}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 5217, \"to\": 5224}, {\"ngram\": \"social injustice\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5280}, {\"ngram\": \"racial inequality\", \"from\": 5285, \"to\": 5302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Essentially, a progressive outlook on a host of issues, specifically on race.\", \"from\": 5344, \"to\": 5421, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Essentially, a progressive outlook\", \"from\": 5344, \"to\": 5378}, {\"ngram\": \"a host\", \"from\": 5382, \"to\": 5388}, {\"ngram\": \"issues\", \"from\": 5392, \"to\": 5398}, {\"ngram\": \"race\", \"from\": 5416, \"to\": 5420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The term began to gain more popularity at the start of the Black Lives Matter movement in 2014, and was used to wake people up to the social injustices of police brutality against the Black community following the fatal police shooting of Michael Brown.\", \"from\": 5423, \"to\": 5676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5662, \"end\": 5675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.264030158908368e-36, \"text\": \"Michael Brown\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shooting_of_Michael_Brown\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The term\", \"from\": 5423, \"to\": 5431}, {\"ngram\": \"more popularity\", \"from\": 5446, \"to\": 5461}, {\"ngram\": \"the start\", \"from\": 5465, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"the Black Lives Matter movement\", \"from\": 5478, \"to\": 5509}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 5540, \"to\": 5546}, {\"ngram\": \"the social injustices\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5574}, {\"ngram\": \"police brutality\", \"from\": 5578, \"to\": 5594}, {\"ngram\": \"the Black community\", \"from\": 5603, \"to\": 5622}, {\"ngram\": \"the fatal police shooting\", \"from\": 5633, \"to\": 5658}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, hardly a bad thing.\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5701, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"So, hardly a bad thing\", \"from\": 5678, \"to\": 5700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The snag is that the word has since been co-opted by conversatives and right-leaners as a pejorative term to signify... well, anything they do not like the sound of.\", \"from\": 5703, \"to\": 5868, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The snag\", \"from\": 5703, \"to\": 5711}, {\"ngram\": \"the word\", \"from\": 5720, \"to\": 5728}, {\"ngram\": \"conversatives\", \"from\": 5756, \"to\": 5769}, {\"ngram\": \"right-leaners\", \"from\": 5774, \"to\": 5787}, {\"ngram\": \"a pejorative term\", \"from\": 5791, \"to\": 5808}, {\"ngram\": \"well, anything\", \"from\": 5823, \"to\": 5837}, {\"ngram\": \"the sound\", \"from\": 5855, \"to\": 5864}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The word \\\"woke\\\" is now a catch-all term used to refer to either insincere or performative activism, or in phrases like \\\"woke ideology\\\" or \\\"the woke agenda\\\" - a dog whistle that allows those who use it to air their grievances about progressive values without deploying more extreme (usually racist) language.\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 6177, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The word\", \"from\": 5870, \"to\": 5878}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"woke\", \"from\": 5879, \"to\": 5884}, {\"ngram\": \"a catch-all term\", \"from\": 5893, \"to\": 5909}, {\"ngram\": \"either insincere or performative activism\", \"from\": 5927, \"to\": 5968}, {\"ngram\": \"phrases\", \"from\": 5976, \"to\": 5983}, {\"ngram\": \"ideology\", \"from\": 5995, \"to\": 6003}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the woke agenda\", \"from\": 6008, \"to\": 6024}, {\"ngram\": \"a dog whistle\", \"from\": 6028, \"to\": 6041}, {\"ngram\": \"their grievances\", \"from\": 6078, \"to\": 6094}, {\"ngram\": \"progressive values\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6119}, {\"ngram\": \"more extreme (usually racist) language\", \"from\": 6138, \"to\": 6176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's frequently trotted out when talking about identity-based social justice issues; the questioning or denunciation of systemic injustices in society; racial education in schools; LGBTQ+ rights... Everything umbrellaed in so-called culture wars.\", \"from\": 6179, \"to\": 6425, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"identity-based social justice issues\", \"from\": 6226, \"to\": 6262}, {\"ngram\": \"the questioning\", \"from\": 6264, \"to\": 6279}, {\"ngram\": \"denunciation\", \"from\": 6283, \"to\": 6295}, {\"ngram\": \"systemic injustices\", \"from\": 6299, \"to\": 6318}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 6322, \"to\": 6329}, {\"ngram\": \"racial education\", \"from\": 6331, \"to\": 6347}, {\"ngram\": \"schools\", \"from\": 6351, \"to\": 6358}, {\"ngram\": \"LGBTQ+ rights\", \"from\": 6360, \"to\": 6373}, {\"ngram\": \"Everything\", \"from\": 6377, \"to\": 6387}, {\"ngram\": \"so-called culture wars\", \"from\": 6402, \"to\": 6424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And now, poster designs.\", \"from\": 6427, \"to\": 6451, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"And now, poster designs\", \"from\": 6427, \"to\": 6450}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gattoni's poster design features a cartoonish Paris cityscape with major landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower and a wealth of tiny details, including all 54 Olympic and Paralympic sports.\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6499, \"end\": 6504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3813483241155323e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 6620, \"end\": 6637, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paralympic sports\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paralympic_sports\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gattoni's poster design\", \"from\": 6453, \"to\": 6476}, {\"ngram\": \"major landmarks\", \"from\": 6520, \"to\": 6535}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 6544, \"to\": 6560}, {\"ngram\": \"a wealth\", \"from\": 6565, \"to\": 6573}, {\"ngram\": \"tiny details\", \"from\": 6577, \"to\": 6589}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In reaction to being pulled into France's culture wars, Gattoni said he had rendered buildings \\\"in the way they come to my mind, without any ulterior motive\\\".\", \"from\": 6640, \"to\": 6798, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6673, \"end\": 6679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.941716133673768, \"rank\": 0.061734972251580505, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reaction\", \"from\": 6643, \"to\": 6651}, {\"ngram\": \"Gattoni\", \"from\": 6696, \"to\": 6703}, {\"ngram\": \"buildings\", \"from\": 6725, \"to\": 6734}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 6739, \"to\": 6746}, {\"ngram\": \"my mind\", \"from\": 6760, \"to\": 6767}, {\"ngram\": \"any ulterior motive\", \"from\": 6777, \"to\": 6796}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was never meant to be accurate - rather an Art Deco fantasy utopia of Paris.\", \"from\": 6800, \"to\": 6879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6846, \"end\": 6854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.791009594464641e-15, \"text\": \"Art Deco\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Art_Deco\"}, {\"beg